snippet.textDisplay: Infringement of the copyright law- @Coke Studio Bangla, @Disha (costume designer). Deora is a beautiful song. I am sure Coke Studio and the costume designer respects the copyright and the moral rights of all the artists involved. It was disheartening to see that my photo of Late Abdur Rahman Boyati is printed on Ghaashphoring Choir's yellow dress (displayed next to the costume designer) without my written permission or consent. This is a clear infringement of the copyright law and the photographer's moral right. This is a well known photo and it is not at all difficult to find the photographer's name, and to reach out for permission. I urge Coke Studio Bangla and the costume designer to acknowledge the photographer and refrain from any further production of this costume and/or any other products (with this photo or part of this photo).
